text: Lukey may refer to: * Len Lukey (died 1978), Australian racing driver, winner of the 1959 Australian Drivers' Championship * T. V. H. Lukey, a co-creator of the English Mastiff dog breed * Lucas "Lukey" Ebenezer Hinks, a character in the comic strip Barney Google and Snuffy Smith * "Lukey's Boat", a comical folk song retitled "Lukey" for the Great Big Sea album Up * Lukey, a brand owned by Tenneco, an American Fortune 500 company
title: Lukey
